==Latin==
===Etymology===
Proto-Indo-European ''*ḱoru'' and ''*ḱr̥-no-'', from ''*ḱer-'' "horn". Cognates include  English [[horn]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈkɔrnuː/}}
X-SAMPA /"kOrnu:/

===Noun===
'''cornū, [[Wiktionary Appendix:Latin fourth declension|-ūs]]''' ''n''
#a [[horn]]
#a [[wing]] of an army

